survey.music_making: Piano from ages 5-10, french horn until high school. Now I just mostly mess around on my guitar and bass, but I am not proficient at either.
survey.activities: Play chess, work, drive, hanging out with friends, housework. Basically everything I do, I will have music on if possible.
survey.genres_ranked.text2: Traditional Folk (mostly late 19th century - early 20th century)
survey.habit_change: Not really. I've always listened to a lot of music and a wide variety of music.
survey.habits: I often seek out music in genres that I don't necessarily like if the album is well received or innovative. I went to my first metal show recently, mostly out of curiosity. I'd say I split my music listening 70-30 between music I truly enjoy and music exploration.
